      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The ideal solution involves a nuanced approach that recognizes the differing economic realities between urban and rural areas. Instead of a single, blanket minimum wage increase, policymakers could implement tiered wage structures based on regional cost of living indexes. This allows businesses in lower cost-of-living towns to remain viable while still providing a meaningful increase in wages for workers everywhere.",
      "source": "target",
